fix_instruction:
In the `clk1_en` always block (triggered on `negedge clk1 or negedge rst_n`), change the reset value from `1'b1` to `1'b0`:

```
if (!rst_n)
    clk1_en <= 1'b0;
```

This ensures both `clk1_en` and `clk2_en` start at 0 on reset, preventing `clkout` from going high immediately at the first clk1 positive edge after reset. The first falling edge of clk1 will then set `clk1_en <= (~sel) & (~clk2_en)`

Replace the second `always @(posedge clk or posedge reset)` block that drives `p_count_o` with a combinational `always @(*)` block: output `count_q` when `sw_req_i` is high, otherwise output zero. Specifically, change the second always block to:

```
always @(*) begin
    if (sw_req_i)
        p_count_o = count_q;
    else
        p_count_o = '0;
end
```

